race.comment: TORONESS (7) switched from a Victorian barn and found one too good on a 29-day return. She's going to improve off that and is still shy of her best. Maps for a soft run and can go one better for the Currie yard. RARE MOON (9) drew wide and got too far back in the same contest. Finished it off strongly and the longer sprint suits. Has the rail today and may settle closer. HABERFIELD (8) has disappointed since the switch from a Sydney yard. Three back he was within range at Kembla Grange over 1400m and he draws better today. Might be ready to show more. STRIKE ME PINK (10) got a mile back last start on debut. Can improve with the benefit of race experience now under the belt.
